  "text_preview": "\"play\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"play\" The word \"play\" has several different signs depending on what you mean. If you mean play as in an \"act\" or a \"drama,\" see: See: THEATER / act / play / drama If you mean \"play\" as in \"playing around\" then you can use the version of this sign that shakes \"Y\" handshapes. PLAY (as in \"play time,\" \"playing,\") Sample sentence: BASKETBALL, YOU LIKE PLAY? (Do you like to play basketball?) PLAYER: To sign \"player\" simply add the \"PERSON / AGENT \" sign to the sign PLAY. PARTY: The sign PLAY happens to be one of the versions of the sign for \"party.\" There are four common ways to sign \"party.\" The point I want to make here though is that you should NOT initialize the sign play with a \"P\" hand. See: PARTY Notes: I've ob"
}
